obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (14169)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14169&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Industries (Development`
  line `and Regulation) Act, 1951.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 51 of 1961, s. 2 (w.e.f. 11-12-1961).`
  line
  line `2. 8th May, 1952, vide notification No. S.R.O. 811 (E), dated 8th May, 1952, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `15th February, 1962, vide notification No. S.R.O. 458/IDRA/1/1/62 (E), in respect of the State of Jammu and Kashmir,`
  line `dated 7th February, 1962, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (14170)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14170&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Union should take under its control the industries specified in the First`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (14171)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14171&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Advisory Council" means the Central Advisory Council established under section 5;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) "ancillary industrial undertaking" means an industrial undertaking which, in accordance`
  line `with the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 11B and the requirements specified under that`
  line `sub-section, is entitled to be regarded as an ancillary industrial undertaking for the purposes of this`
  line Act;]
  line
  line ^2[
  line `^3[(ab)] "current assets" means bank balances and cash and includes such other assets or`
  line `reserves as are expected to be realised in cash or sold or consumed within a period of not more than`
  line `twelve months in the ordinary course of business, such as, stock-in-trade, amounts due from sundry`
  line `debtorsfor sale of goods and for services rendered, advance tax payments and bills receivable,`
  line `butdoes not include sums credited to a provident fund, a pension fund, a gratuity fund or any other`
  line `fund for the welfare of the employees, maintained by a company owning an industrial undertaking;`
  line
  line `^3[(ac)]"current liabilities" means liabilities which must be met on demand or within a period of`
  line `twelve months from the date they are incurred; and includes any current liability which is suspended`
  line `under section 18FB;]`
  line
  line `(b) "Development Council" means a Development Council established under section 6;`
  line
  line `^4[(bb) "existing industrial undertaking" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an industrial undertaking pertaining to any of the industries specified in the`
  line `First Schedule as originally enacted, an industrial undertaking which was in existence on the`
  line `commencement of this Act or for the establishment of which effective steps had been taken`
  line `before such commencement, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an industrial undertaking pertaining to any of the industries added to`
  line `the First Schedule by an amendment thereof, an industrial undertaking which is in existence on`
  line `the coming into force of such amendment or for the establishment of which effective steps had`
  line `been taken before the coming into force of such amendment;]`
  line
  line `(c) "factory" means any premises, including the precincts thereof, in any part of which a`
  line `manufacturing process is being carried on or is ordinarily so carried on--`
  line
  line `(i) with the aid of power, provided that fifty or more workers are working or were working`
  line `thereon on any day of the preceding twelve months; or`
  line
  line `(ii) without the aid of power, provided that one hundred or more workers are working or`
  line `were working thereon on any day of the preceding twelve months and provided further that in no`
  line `part of such premises any manufacturing process is being carried on with the aid of power;`
  line
  line `^5[(cc) "High Court" means the High Court having jurisdiction in relation to the place at which the`
  line `registered office of a company is situate;]`
  line
  line `(d) "industrial undertaking" means any undertaking pertaining to a scheduled industry carried`
  line `on in one or more factories by any person or authority including Government;`
  line
  line `^6[(dd) "new article", in relation to an industrial undertaking which is registered or in respect of`
  line `which a licence or permission has been issued under this Act, means--`
  line
  line `(a) any article which falls under an item in the First Schedule other than the item under which`
  line `articles ordinarily manufactured or produced in the industrial undertaking at the date of`
  line `registration or issue of the licence or permission, as the case may be, fall;`
  line
  line `(b) any article which bears a mark as defined in the Trade Marks Act, 1940 (5 of 1940), or`
  line `which is the subject of a patent, if at the date of registration or issue of the licence or permission, as the`
  line `case may be, the industrial undertaking was not manufacturing or producing such article bearing`
  line `that mark or which is the subject of that patent;]`
  line
  line `(e) "notified order" means an order notified in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "owner" in relation to an industrial undertaking means the person who, or the authority`
  line `which, has the ultimate control over the affairs of the undertaking, and, where the said affairs are`
  line `entrusted to a manager, managing director or managing agent, such manager, managing director or`
  line `managing agent shall be deemed to be the owner of the undertaking;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "Schedule" means a Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "scheduled industry" means any of the industries specified in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `^7[(j) "small scale industrial undertaking" means an industrial undertaking which, in accordance`
  line `with the requirements specified under sub-section (1) of section 11B, is entitled to be regarded as a`
  line `small scale industrial undertaking for the purposes of this Act;]`
  line
  line ^5[
  line `^8[(k)] words and expressions used herein but not defined in this Act and defined in the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-1-1984).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3 Clauses (aa) and (ab) re-lettered as clause (ab) and (ac) thereof by Act 4 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-1-1984).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `7 Ins. by Act 4 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  line
  line `8 Clause (j) re-lettered as clause (k) thereof by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-1-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (14172)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14172&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `[Saving.]--Omitted by the Industries (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 1953 (26 of`
  line `1953), s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (14173)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Establishment and constitution of Central Advisory Council and its functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by Act 26 of 1953, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14173&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purpose of advising it on matters concerning the development and regulation of scheduled industries, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notified order, establish a Council to be called the Central Advisory`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Council shall consist of a Chairman and such other members, not exceeding thirty`
  line `in number, all of whom shall be appointed by the Central Government from among persons who are in its`
  line `opinion capable of representing the interests of--`
  line
  line `(a) owners of industrial undertakings in scheduled industries;`
  line
  line `(b) persons employed in industrial undertakings in scheduled industries;`
  line
  line `(c) consumers of goods manufactured or produced by scheduled industries;`
  line
  line `(d) such other class of persons including primary producers, as in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, ought to be represented on the Advisory Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of, the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, and the`
  line `manner of filling casual vacancies among, members of the Advisory Council, shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall consult the Advisory Council in regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the making of any rules, other than the first rules to be made under sub-section (3);`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `and may consult the Advisory Council in regard to any other matter connected with the administration of`
  line `this Act in respect of which the Central Government may consider it necessary to obtain the advice of the`
  line `Advisory Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (14174)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Establishment and constitution of Development Councils and their functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14174&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, by notified order establish for any scheduled industry or group of scheduled`
  line `industries, a body of persons to be called a Development Council which shall consist of members who in`
  line `the opinion of the Central Government are--`
  line
  line `(a) persons capable of representing the interests of owners of industrial undertakings in the`
  line `scheduled industry or group of scheduled industries;`
  line
  line `(b) persons having special knowledge of matters relating to the technical or other aspects of the`
  line `scheduled industry or group of scheduled industries;`
  line
  line `(c) persons capable of representing the interests of persons employed in industrial undertakings in`
  line `the scheduled industry or group of scheduled industries;`
  line
  line `(d) persons not belonging to any of the aforesaid categories, who are capable of representing the`
  line `interests of consumers of goods manufactured or produced by the scheduled industry or group of`
  line `scheduled industries.`
  line
  line `(2) The number and the term of office of, and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their`
  line `functions by, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among members of a Development Council shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Development Council shall be, by virtue of this Act, a body corporate by such name as may`
  line `be specified in the notified order establishing it and may hold and transfer property and shall by the said`
  line `name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(4) A Development Council shall perform such functions of a kind specified in the Second Schedule`
  line `as may be assigned to it by the Central Government and for whose exercise by the Development Council`
  line `it appears to the Central Government expedient to provide in order to increase the efficiency or`
  line `productivity in the scheduled industry or group of scheduled industries for which the Development`
  line `Council is established, to improve or develop the service that such industry or group of industries renders`
  line `or could render to the community, or to enable such industry or group of industries to render such service`
  line `more economically.`
  line
  line `(5) A Development Council shall also perform such other functions as it may be required to perform`
  line `by or under any other provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (14175)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Reports and accounts of Development Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14175&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Development Council shall prepare and`
  line `transmit to the Central Government and the Advisory Council, annually, a report setting out what has`
  line `been done in the discharge of its functions during the financial year last completed.`
  line
  line `(2) The report shall include a statement of the accounts of the Development Council for that year, and`
  line `shall be transmitted as soon as accounts therefor have been audited, together with a copy of any report`
  line `made by the auditors on the accounts.`
  line
  line `(3) The statement of account shall be in such form as may be prescribed, being a form which shall`
  line `conform to the best commercial standards, and the statement shall show the total of remuneration and`
  line `allowances paid during the year to members and officers of the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of each such report of a Development Council, or made by the auditors on its accounts,`
  line `shall be laid before Parliament by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (14176)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Dissolution of Development Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14176&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, if it is satisfied that a`
  line `Development Council should cease to continue in being, by notified order, dissolve that Development`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) On the dissolution of a Development Council under sub-section (1), the assets of the Development`
  line `Council, after its liabilities, if any, are met therefrom, shall vest in the Central Government for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (14177)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Imposition of cess on scheduled industries in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14177&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There may be levied and`
  line `collected as a cess for the purposes of this Act on all goods manufactured or produced in any such`
  line `scheduled industry as may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government by notified order a duty`
  line `of excise at such rate as may be specified in the notified order, and different rates may be specified for`
  line `different goods or different classes of goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rate shall in any case exceed two annas per cent. of the value of the goods.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section, the expression "value" in relation to any goods shall be deemed to`
  line `be the wholesale cash price for which such goods of the like kind and quality are sold or are capable of`
  line `being sold for delivery at the place of manufacture and at the time of their removal therefrom, without any`
  line `abatement or deduction whatever except trade discount and the amount of duty then payable.`
  line
  line `(2) The cess shall be payable at such intervals, within such time and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, and any rules made in this behalf may provide for the grant of a rebate for prompt payment of`
  line `the cess.`
  line
  line `(3) The said cess may be recovered in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may hand over the proceeds of the cess collected under this section in`
  line `respect of the goods manufactured or produced by any scheduled industry or group of scheduled`
  line `industries to the Development Council established for that industry or group of industries, and where it`
  line `does so, the Development Council shall utilise the said proceeds--`
  line
  line `(a) to promote scientific and industrial research with reference to the scheduled industry or group`
  line `of scheduled industries in respect of which the Development Council is established;`
  line
  line `(b) to promote improvements in design and quality with reference to the products of such industry`
  line `or group of industries;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide for the training of technicians and labour in such industry or group of industries;`
  line
  line `(d) to meet such expenses in the exercise of its functions and its administrative expenses as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (14178)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Registration of existing industrial undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14178&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The owner of every existing industrial`
  line `undertaking, not being the Central Government, shall, within such period as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, fix in this behalf with respect to industrial undertakings generally`
  line `or with respect to any class of them, register the undertaking in the prescribed manner.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall also cause to be registered in the same manner every existing`
  line `industrial undertaking of which it is the owner.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Where an industrial undertaking is registered under this section, there shall be issued to the`
  line `owner of the undertaking or the Central Government, as the case may be, a certificate of registration`
  line `^3[containing the productive capacity of the industrial undertaking and such other particulars as may be`
  line prescribed].]
  line
  line `^4[(4) The owner of every industrial undertaking to whom a certificate of registration has been issued`
  line `under this section before the commencement of the Industries (Development and Regulation) Amendment`
  line `Act, 1973 (67 of 1973), shall, if the undertaking falls within such class of undertakings as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, produce, within such`
  line `period as may be specified in such notification, the certificate of registration for entering therein the`
  line `productive capacity of the industrial undertaking and other prescribed particulars.`
  line
  line `(5) In specifying the productive capacity in any certificate of registration issued under sub-section (3),`
  line `the Central Government shall take into consideration the productive or installed capacity of the industrial`
  line `undertaking as specified in the application for registration made under sub-section (1), the level of`
  line `production immediately before the date on which the application for registration was made under subsection`
  line `(1), the level of the highest annual production during the three years immediately preceding the`
  line `introduction in Parliament of the Industries (Development and Regulation) Amendment Bill, 1973, the`
  line `extent to which production during the said period was utilised for export and such other factors as the`
  line `Central Government may consider relevant including the extent of under-utilisation of capacity, if any,`
  line `during the relevant period due to any cause.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 5, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1973, s. 2, for "containing such particulars as may be prescribed" (w.e.f. 7-2-1974).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-2-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (14179)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Revocation of registration in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14179&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Revocation of registration in certain cases.--If the Central Government is satisfied that the`
  line `registration of any industrial undertaking has been obtained by misrepresentation as to an essential fact or`
  line `that any industrial undertaking has ceased to be registrable under this Act by reason of any exemption`
  line `granted under this Act becoming applicable thereto or that for any other reason the registration has`
  line `become useless or ineffective and therefore requires to be revoked, the Central Government may after`
  line `giving an opportunity to the owner of the undertaking to be heard revoke the registration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (14180)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Licensing of new industrial undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14180&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person or authority other than the Central`
  line `Government, shall, after the commencement of this Act, establish any new industrial undertaking, except`
  line `under and in accordance with a licence issued in that behalf by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Government other than the Central Government may, with the previous permission of`
  line `the Central Government, establish a new industrial undertaking.`
  line
  line `(2) A licence or permission under sub-section (1) may contain such conditions including, in`
  line `particular, conditions as to the location of the undertaking and the minimum standards in respect of size to`
  line `be provided therein as the Central Government may deem fit to impose in accordance with the rules, if`
  line `any, made under section 30.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (14181)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 13
  title `Licence for producing or manufacturing new articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. byAct 26 of 1953, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14181&sectionno=11A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Licence for producing or manufacturing new articles.--The owner of an industrial`
  line `undertaking not being the Central Government which is registered under section 10 or in respect of which`
  line `a licence or permission has been issued under section 11 shall not produce or manufacture any new article`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an industrial undertaking registered under section 10, he has obtained a licence`
  line `for producing or manufacturing such new article; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an industrial undertaking in respect of which a licence or permission has been`
  line `issued under section 11, he has had the existing licence or permission amended in the prescribed`
  line manner.]
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (14182)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Central Government to specify the requirements which shall be complied with by small scale industrial undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1984, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-1-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14182&sectionno=11B&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B.Power of Central Government to specify the requirements which shall be complied with`
  line `by small scale industrial undertakings.--(1) The Central Government may, with a view to ascertaining`
  line `which ancillary and small scale industrial undertakings need supportive measures, exemptions or other`
  line `favourable treatment under this Act to enable them to maintain their viability and strength and so as to be`
  line `effective in--`
  line
  line `(a) promoting in a harmonious manner the industrial economy of the country and easing the`
  line `problem of unemployment, and`
  line
  line `(b) securing that the ownership and control of the material resources of the community are so`
  line `distributed as best to subserve the common good,`
  line
  line `specify, having regard to the factors mentioned in sub-section (2), by notified order, the requirements`
  line `which shall be complied with by an industrial undertaking to enable it to be regarded, for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, as an ancillary, or a small scale, industrial undertaking and different requirements may be so`
  line `specified for different purposes or with respect to industrial undertakings engaged in the manufacture or`
  line `production of different articles:`
  line
  line `Provided that no industrial undertaking shall be regarded as an ancillary industrial undertaking unless`
  line `it is, or is proposed to be, engaged in--`
  line
  line `(i) the manufacture of parts, components, sub-assemblies, toolings or intermediates; or`
  line
  line `(ii) rendering of services, or supplying or rendering, not more than fifty per cent. of its production`
  line `or its total services, as the case may be, to other units for production of other articles.`
  line
  line `(2) The factors referred to in sub-section (1) are the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the investment by the industrial undertaking in--`
  line
  line `(i) plant and machinery, or`
  line
  line `(ii) land, buildings, plant and machinery;`
  line
  line `(b) the nature of ownership of the industrial undertakings;`
  line
  line `(c) the smallness of the number of the workers employed in the industrial undertaking;`
  line
  line `(d) the nature, cost and quality of the product of the industrial undertaking;`
  line
  line `(e) foreign exchange, if any, required for the import of any plant or machinery by the industrial`
  line `undertaking; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other relevant factors as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every notified order proposed to be made under sub-section (1) shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `disapproving the issue of the proposed notified order or both Houses agree in making any modification in`
  line `the proposed notified order, the notified order shall not be made, or, as the case may be, shall be made`
  line `only in such modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an industrial undertaking which, according`
  line `to the law for the time being in force, fell, immediately before the commencement of the Industries`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 1984 (4 of 1984), under the definition of an ancillary, or`
  line `small scale, industrial undertaking, shall, after such commencement, continue to be regarded as an`
  line `ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertaking for the purposes of this Act until the definition aforesaid is`
  line `altered or superseded by any notified order made under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (14183)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `Revocation and amendment of licences in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14183&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied, either on a reference made to it in this behalf or otherwise, that any person or authority, to`
  line `whom or to which, a licence has been issued under section 11, has, without reasonable cause, failed to`
  line `establish or to take effective steps to establish the new industrial undertaking in respect of which the`
  line `licence has been issued within the time specified therefor or within such extended time as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit to grant in any case, it may revoke the licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the Central Government may also vary or`
  line `amend any licence issued under section 11:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such power shall be exercised after effective steps have been taken to establish the`
  line `new industrial undertaking in accordance with the licence issued in this behalf.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The provisions of this section shall apply in relation to a licence issued under section 11A or`
  line `where a licence has been amended under that section, to the amendment thereof, as they apply in relation`
  line `to a licence issued under section 11.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (14184)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Further provision for licensing of industrial undertakings in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14184&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Further provision for licensing of industrial undertakings in special cases.--(1) No owner`
  line `of an industrial undertaking, other than the Central Government, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an industrial undertaking required to be registered under section 10, but which`
  line `has not been registered within the time fixed for the purpose under that section, carry on the business`
  line `of that undertaking after the expiry of such period, or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an industrial undertaking the registration in respect of which has been revoked`
  line `under section 10A`
  line `^2***, carry on the business of the undertaking after the revocation, or`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of an industrial undertaking to which the provisions of this Act did not originally`
  line `apply but became applicable after the commencement of this Act for any reason, carry on the`
  line `business of the undertaking after the expiry of three months from the date on which the provisions of`
  line `this Act became so applicable, or`
  line
  line `(d) effect any substantial expansion of an industrial undertaking which has been registered^3[or in`
  line `respect of which a licence or permission has been issued], or`
  line
  line `(e) change the location of the whole or any part of an industrial undertaking which has been`
  line registered,
  line
  line `except under, and in accordance with, a licence issued in that behalf by the Central Government, and, in`
  line `the case of a State Government, except under and in accordance with the previous permission of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11 and of section 12 shall apply, so far as may be, in`
  line `relation to the issue of licences or permissions to any industrial undertaking referred to in this section as`
  line `they apply in relation to the issue of licences or permissions to a new industrial undertaking.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "substantial expansion" means the expansion of an`
  line `existing industrial undertaking which substantially increases the productive capacity of the undertaking,`
  line `or which is of such a nature as to amount virtually to a new industrial undertaking, but does not include`
  line `any such expansion as is normal to the undertaking having regard to its nature and the circumstances`
  line `relating to such expansion.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for section 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. The words "on the ground that it had been obtained by misrepresentation as to an essential fact" omitted by`
  line `Act 71 of 1956, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (14185)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Procedure for the grant of licence or permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14185&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Before granting any licence or permission`
  line `under ^1[section 11, section 11A`
  line `^2[section 13 or section 29B]], the Central Government may require such`
  line `officer or authority as it may appoint for the purpose, to make a full and complete investigation in respect`
  line `of applications received in this behalf and report to it the result of such investigation and in making any`
  line `such investigation, the officer or authority shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 10, for "section 11 or section 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 71 of 1956, s. 3, for "or section 13" (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (14186)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to cause investigation to be made into scheduled industries or industrial undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 11, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14186&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central Government is of the opinion that--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of any scheduled industry or industrial undertaking or undertakings--`
  line
  line `(i) there has been, or is likely to be, a substantial fall in the volume of production in respect of`
  line `any article or class of articles relatable to that industry or manufactured or produced in the`
  line `industrial undertaking or undertakings, as the case may be; for which, having regard to the`
  line `economic conditions prevailing, there is no justification; or`
  line
  line `(ii) there has been, or is likely to be, a marked deterioration in the quality of any article or`
  line `class of articles relatable to that industry or manufactured or produced in the industrial`
  line `undertaking or undertakings, as the case may be, which could have been or can be avoided; or`
  line
  line `(iii) there has been or is likely to be a rise in the price of any article or class of articles`
  line `relatable to that industry or manufactured or produced in the industrial undertaking or`
  line `undertakings, as the case may be, for which there is no justification; or`
  line
  line `(iv) it is necessary to take any such action as is provided in this Chapter for the purpose of`
  line `conserving any resources of national importance which are utilised in the industry or the`
  line `industrial undertaking or undertakings, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `^1[(b) any industrial undertaking is being managed in a manner highly detrimental to the scheduled`
  line `industry concerned or to public interest;]`
  line
  line `the Central Government may make or cause to be made a full and complete investigation into the`
  line `circumstances of the case by such person or body of persons as it may appoint for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (14187)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to investigate into the affairs of a company in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14187&sectionno=15A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Power to investigate into the affairs of a company in liquidation.--(1) Where a company,`
  line `owning an industrial undertaking is being wound up by or under the supervision of the High Court, and`
  line `the business of such company is not being continued, the Central Government may, if it is of opinion that`
  line `it is necessary, in the interests of the general public and, in particular, in the interests of production,`
  line `supply or distribution of articles or class of articles relatable to the concerned scheduled industry, to`
  line `investigate into the possibility of running or re-starting the industrial undertaking, make an application to`
  line `the High Court praying for permission to make, or cause to be made, an investigation into such possibility`
  line `by such person or body of persons as that Government may appoint for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application is made by the Central Government under sub-section (1), the High Court`
  line `shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, grant the permission prayed for.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (14188)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers of Central Government on completion of investigation under section 15.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14188&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If after`
  line `making or causing to be made any such investigation as is referred to in section 15 the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that action under this section is desirable, it may issue such directions to the`
  line `industrial undertaking or undertakings concerned as may be appropriate in the circumstances for all or`
  line `any of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the production of any article or class of articles by the industrial undertaking or`
  line `undertakings and fixing the standards of production;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the industrial undertaking or undertakings to take such steps as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary to stimulate the development of the industry to which the`
  line `undertaking or undertakings relates or relate;`
  line
  line `(c) prohibiting the industrial undertaking or undertakings from resorting to any act or practice`
  line `which might reduce its or their production, capacity or economic value;`
  line
  line `(d) controlling the prices, or regulating the distribution, of any article or class of articles which`
  line `have been the subject-matter of investigation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a case relating to any industry or industrial undertaking or undertakings is under`
  line `investigation, the Central Government may issue at any time any direction of the nature referred to in subsection`
  line `(1) to the industrial undertaking or undertakings concerned , and any such direction shall have`
  line `effect until it is varied or revoked by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (14189)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14189&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `[Special provisions for direct control by Central Government in certain cases.]-- Omitted by`
  line `the Industries (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 1953 (26 of 1953), s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (14190)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of person or body of persons appointed under section 15 to call for assistance in any investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14190&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The person or body of persons appointed to make any investigation under section 15`
  line `^24[or section 15A] may choose one or more persons possessing special knowledge of any matter relating to`
  line `the investigation to assist him or it in holding the investigation.`
  line
  line `(2) The person or body of persons so appointed shall have all the powers of a civil court under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the purpose of taking evidence on oath (which he or it is`
  line `hereby empowered to administer) and of enforcing the attendance of witnesses and compelling the`
  line `production of documents and material objects, and the person or body of persons shall be deemed to be a`
  line `civil court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXXV of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1898 (5 of 1898).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (14191)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Central Government to assume management or control of an industrial undertaking in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14191&sectionno=18A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Power of Central Government to assume management or control of an industrial`
  line `undertaking in certain cases.--(1) If the Central Government is of opinion that--`
  line
  line `(a) an industrial undertaking to which directions have been issued in pursuance of section 16 has`
  line `failed to comply with such directions, or`
  line
  line `(b) an industrial undertaking in respect of which an investigation has been made under section 15`
  line `(whether or not any directions have been issued to the undertaking in pursuance of section 16), is`
  line `being managed in a manner highly detrimental to the scheduled industry concerned or to public`
  line interest,
  line `the Central Government may, by notified order, authorise any person or body of persons to take over the`
  line `management of the whole or any part of the undertaking or to exercise in respect of the whole or any part`
  line `of the undertaking such functions of control as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Any notified order issued under sub-section (1) shall have effect for such period not exceeding`
  line `five years as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that if the Central Government is of opinion that it is expedient in the public interest that`
  line `any such notified order should continue to have effect after the expiry of the period of five years`
  line `aforesaid, it may from time to time issue directions for such continuance for such period, not exceeding`
  line `two years at a time, as may be specified in the direction, so however that the total period of such`
  line `continuance (after the expiry of the said period of five years) does not exceed ^3[twelve years]; and where`
  line `any such direction is issued, a copy thereof shall be laid, as soon as may be, before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.]
  line
  line `Explanation.--The power to authorise a body of persons under this section to take over the`
  line `management of an industrial undertaking which is a company includes also a power to appoint any`
  line `individual, firm or company to be the managing agent of the industrial undertaking on such terms and`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may think fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 1965, s. 2, for the proviso (w.e.f. 29-3-1965).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1974, s. 2, for "ten years" (w.e.f. 29-6-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_aa:
  sectionId (14192)
  sectionNo 18AA
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to take over industrial undertakings without investigation under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14192&sectionno=18AA&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[18AA. Power to take over industrial undertakings without investigation under certain`
  line `circumstances.-- (1) Without prejudice to any other provision of this Act, if, from the documentary or`
  line `other evidence in its possession, the Central Government is satisfied, in relation to an industrial`
  line `undertaking, that--`
  line
  line `(a) the persons in charge of such industrial undertaking have, by reckless investments or creation`
  line `of incumbrances on the assets of the industrial undertaking, or by diversion of funds, brought about a`
  line `situation which is likely to affect the production of articles manufactured or produced in the industrial`
  line `undertaking, and that immediate action is necessary to prevent such a situation; or`
  line
  line `(b) it has been closed for a period of not less than three months (whether by reason of the`
  line `voluntary winding up of the company owning the industrial undertaking or for any other reason) and`
  line `such closure is prejudicial to the concerned scheduled industry and that the financial condition of the`
  line `company owning the industrial undertaking and the condition of the plant and machinery of such`
  line `undertaking are such that it is possible to re-start the undertaking and such re-starting is necessary in`
  line `the interests of the general public,`
  line
  line `it may, by a notified order, authorise any person or body of persons (hereafter referred to as the`
  line `"authorised person") to take over the management of the whole or any part of the industrial undertaking`
  line `or to exercise in respect of the whole or any part of the undertaking such functions of control as may be`
  line `specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (2) of section 18A shall, as far as may be, apply to a notified order`
  line `made under sub-section (1) as they apply to a notified order made under sub-section (1) of section 18A.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) shall apply to an industrial undertaking`
  line `owned by a company which is being wound up by or under the supervision of the Court.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any notified order has been made under sub-section (1), the person or body of persons`
  line `having for the time being, charge of the management or control of the industrial undertaking, whether by`
  line `or under the orders of any court or any contract, instrument or otherwise, shall, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in such order, contract, instrument or other arrangements forthwith make over the charge of`
  line `management or control, as the case may be, of the industrial undertaking to the authorised person.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of sections 18B to 18E (both inclusive) shall, as far as may be, apply to, or in`
  line `relation to, the industrial undertaking, in respect of which a notified order has been made under subsection`
  line `(1), as they apply to an industrial undertaking in relation to which a notified order has been issued`
  line `under section 18A.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_b:
  sectionId (14193)
  sectionNo 18B
  orderNo 25
  title `Effect of notified order under section 18A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14193&sectionno=18B&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[18B. Effect of notified order under section 18A.--(1) On the issue of a notified order under section`
  line `18A authorising the taking over of the management of an industrial undertaking,`
  line
  line `(a) all persons in charge of the management, including persons holding office as managers or`
  line `directors of the industrial undertaking immediately before the issue of the notified order, shall be`
  line `deemed to have vacated their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) any contract of management between the industrial undertaking and any managing agent or`
  line `any director thereof holding office as such immediately before the issue of the notified order shall be`
  line `deemed to have been terminated;`
  line
  line `(c) the managing agent, if any, appointed under section 18A shall be deemed to have been duly`
  line `appointed as the managing agent in pursuance of the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913), and`
  line `the memorandum and articles of association of the industrial undertaking, and the provisions of the`
  line `said Act and of the memorandum and articles shall, subject to the other provisions contained in this`
  line `Act, apply accordingly, but no such managing agent shall be removed from office except with the`
  line `previous consent of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) the person or body of persons authorised under section 18A to take over the management shall`
  line `take all such steps as may be necessary to take into his or their custody or control all the property,`
  line `effects and actionable claims to which the industrial undertaking is or appears to be entitled, and all`
  line `the property and effects of the industrial undertaking shall be deemed to be in the custody of the`
  line `person or, as the case may be, the body of persons as from the date of the notified order; and`
  line
  line `(e) the persons, if any, authorised under section 18A to take over the management of an industrial`
  line `undertaking which is a company shall be for all purposes the directors of the industrial undertaking`
  line `duly constituted under the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913), and shall alone be entitled to`
  line `exercise all the powers of the directors of the industrial undertaking, whether such powers are derived`
  line `from the said Act or from the memorandum or articles of association of the industrial undertaking or`
  line `from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act and to the control of the Central Government,`
  line `the person or body of persons authorised to take over the management of an industrial undertaking, shall`
  line `take such steps as may be necessary for the purpose of efficiently managing the business of the industrial`
  line `undertaking and shall exercise such other powers and have such other duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person or body of persons has been authorised to exercise any functions of control in`
  line `relation to an industrial undertaking, the undertaking shall be carried on pursuant to any directions given`
  line `by the authorised person in accordance with the provisions of the notified order, and any person having`
  line `any functions of management in relation to the undertaking or part thereof shall comply with all such`
  line directions.
  line
  line `(4) The person or body of persons authorised under section ^2[18A] shall, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the memorandum or articles of association of the industrial undertaking, exercise his or their`
  line `functions in accordance with such directions as may be given by the Central Government so, however,`
  line `that he or they shall not have any power to give any other person any directions under this section`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of any Act or instrument determining the functions of the authority`
  line `carrying on the undertaking except in so far as may be specifically provided by the notified order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1957, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "18" (w.e.f. 17-9-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_c:
  sectionId (14194)
  sectionNo 18C
  orderNo 26
  title `Contracts in bad faith, etc., may be cancelled or varied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14194&sectionno=18C&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[18C. Contracts in bad faith, etc., may be cancelled or varied.--Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions contained in section 18B, the person or body of persons authorised under section 18A to take`
  line `over the management of an industrial undertaking may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, make an application to any court having jurisdiction in this behalf for the purpose of`
  line `cancelling or varying any contract or agreement entered into, at any time before the issue of the notified`
  line `order under section 18A, between the industrial undertaking and any other person and the court may, if`
  line `satisfied after due inquiry that such contract or agreement had been entered into in bad faith and is`
  line `detrimental to the interests of the industrial undertaking, make an order cancelling or varying (either`
  line `unconditionally or subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose) that contract or agreement, and`
  line `the contract or agreement shall have effect accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_d:
  sectionId (14195)
  sectionNo 18D
  orderNo 27
  title `No right to compensation for termination of office or contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14195&sectionno=18D&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[18D. No right to compensation for termination of office or contract.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any law for the time being in force, no person who ceases to hold any office by reason of the`
  line `provisions contained in clause (a) of section 18B, or whose contract of management is terminated by`
  line `reason of the provisions contained in clause (b) of that section, shall be entitled to any compensation for`
  line `the loss of office or for the premature termination of his contract of management:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the right of any such person to recover`
  line `from the industrial undertaking moneys recoverable otherwise than by way of such compensation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_e:
  sectionId (14196)
  sectionNo 18E
  orderNo 28
  title `Application of Act 7 of 1913.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14196&sectionno=18E&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[18E. Application of Act 7 of 1913.--(1) Where the management of an industrial undertaking, being`
  line `a company as defined in the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913) is taken over by the Central`
  line `Government, then, notwithstanding anything contained in the said Act or in the memorandum or articles`
  line `of association of such undertaking,--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall not be lawful for the shareholders of such undertaking or any other person to nominate`
  line `or appoint any person to be a director of the undertaking;`
  line
  line `(b) no resolution passed at any meeting of the shareholders of such undertaking shall be given`
  line `effect to unless approved by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) no proceeding for the winding up of such undertaking or for the appointment of a receiver in`
  line `respect thereof shall lie in any court except with the consent of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), and to the other provisions contained in this`
  line `Act and subject to such other exceptions, restrictions and limitations, if any, as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of`
  line `1913), shall continue to apply to such undertaking in the same manner as it applied thereto before the`
  line `issue of the notified order under section 18A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_f:
  sectionId (14197)
  sectionNo 18F
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of Central Government to cancel notified order under section 18A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14197&sectionno=18F&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[18F. Power of Central Government to cancel notified order under section 18A.--If at any time it`
  line `appears to the Central Government on the application of the owner of the industrial undertaking or`
  line `otherwise that the purpose of the order made under section 18A has been fulfilled or that for any other`
  line `reason it is not necessary that the order should remain in force, the Central Government may, by notified`
  line `order, cancel such order and on the cancellation of any such order the management or the control, as the`
  line `case may be, of the industrial undertaking shall vest in the owner of the undertaking.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fa:
  sectionId (14198)
  sectionNo 18FA
  orderNo 30
  title `Power of Central Government to authorise, with the permission of the High Court, persons to take over management or control of industrial undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_fa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14198&sectionno=18FA&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fa_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FA. Power of Central Government to authorise, with the permission of the High Court,`
  line `persons to take over management or control of industrial undertakings.-- (1) If the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that there are possibilities of running or re-starting an industrial undertaking, in`
  line `relation to which an investigation has been made under section 15A, and that such industrial undertaking`
  line `should be run or re-started, as the case may be, for maintaining or increasing the production, supply or`
  line `distribution of articles or class of articles relatable to the scheduled industry, needed by the general`
  line `public, that Government may make an application to the High Court praying for permission to appoint`
  line `any person or body of persons to take over the management of the industrial undertaking or to exercise in`
  line `respect of the whole or any part of the industrial undertaking such functions of control as may be`
  line `specified in the application.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application is made under sub-section (1), the High Court shall make an order`
  line `empowering the Central Government to authorise any person or body of persons (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as the "authorised person",) to take over the management of the industrial undertaking or to exercise`
  line `functions of control in relation to the whole or any part of the industrial undertaking (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as the "concerned part") for a period not exceeding five years:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government is of opinion that it is expedient in the interests of the general`
  line `public that the authorised person should continue to manage the industrial undertaking, or continue to`
  line `exercise functions of control in relation to the concerned part, as the case may be, after the expiry of the`
  line `period of five years aforesaid, it may make an application to the High Court for the continuance of such`
  line `management or functions of control, for such period, not exceeding two years at a time, as may be`
  line `specified in the application and thereupon the High Court may make an order permitting the authorised`
  line `person to continue to manage the industrial undertaking or to exercise functions of control in relation to`
  line `the concerned part:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the total period of such continuance (after the expiry of the initial period of five`
  line `years) shall not, in any case, be permitted to exceed ^2[twelve years].`
  line
  line `(3) Where an order has been made by the High Court under sub-section (2), the High Court shall`
  line `direct the Official Liquidator or any other person having, for the time being, charge of the management or`
  line `control of the industrial undertaking, whether by or under the orders of any Court, or any contract or`
  line `instrument or otherwise, to make over the management of such undertaking or the concerned part, as the`
  line `case may be, to the authorised person and thereupon the authorised person shall be deemed to be the`
  line `Official Liquidator in respect of the industrial undertaking or the concerned part, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Before making over the possession of the industrial undertaking or the concerned part to the`
  line `authorised person, the Official Liquidator shall make a complete inventory of all the assets and liabilities`
  line `of the industrial undertaking or the concerned part, as the case may be, in the manner specified in section`
  line `18FG and deliver a copy of such inventory to the authorised person, who shall, after verifying the`
  line `correctness thereof, sign on the duplicate copy thereof as evidence of the receipt of the inventory by him.`
  line
  line `(5) On taking over the management of the industrial undertaking, or on the commencement of the`
  line `exercise of functions of control in relation to the concerned part, the authorised person shall take`
  line `immediate steps to so run the industrial undertaking or the concerned part as to ensure the maintenance of`
  line production.
  line
  line `(6) The authorised person may, on such terms and conditions and subject to such limitations or`
  line `restrictions as may be prescribed, raise any loan for the purpose of running the industrial undertaking or`
  line `the concerned part, and may, for that purpose, create a floating charge on the current assets of the`
  line `industrial undertaking or the concerned part, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the authorised person is of opinion that the replacement or repair of any machinery of the`
  line `industrial undertaking or the concerned part is necessary for the purpose of efficient running of the`
  line `industrial undertaking or such part, he shall, on such terms and conditions and subject to such limitations`
  line `or restrictions as may be prescribed, make such replacement or repair, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(8) The loan obtained by the authorised person shall be recovered from the assets of the industrial`
  line `undertaking or the concerned part, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) For the purpose of running the industrial undertaking, or exercising functions of control in relation`
  line `to the concerned part, the authorised person may employ such of the former employees of the industrial`
  line `undertaking whose services became discharged by reason of the windingup of the company owning such`
  line `undertaking and every such person employed by the authorised person shall be deemed to have entered`
  line `into a fresh contract of service with the company.--`
  line
  line `(10) The proceedings in the windingup of the company in so far as they relate to`
  line
  line `(a) the industrial undertaking, the management of which has been taken over by the authorised`
  line `person under this section, or`
  line
  line `(b) the concerned part in relation to which any function of control is exercised by the authorised`
  line `person under this section,`
  line
  line `shall, during the period of such management or control, remain stayed, and, in computing the period of`
  line `limitation for the enforcement of any right, privilege, obligation or liability in relation to such undertaking`
  line `or the concerned part, the period during which such proceedings remained stayed shall be excluded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1974, s. 2, for "ten years" (w.e.f. 29-6-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fb:
  sectionId (14199)
  sectionNo 18FB
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of Central Government to make certain declarations in relation to industrial undertakings, the management or control of which has been taken over under section 18A, section 18AA or section 18FA.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_fb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14199&sectionno=18FB&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fb_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FB. Power of Central Government to make certain declarations in relation to industrial`
  line `undertakings, the management or control of which has been taken over under section 18A, section`
  line `18AA or section 18FA.--(1) The Central Government may, if it is satisfied, in relation to an industrial`
  line `undertaking or any part thereof, the management or control of which has been taken over under section`
  line `18A, whether before or after the commencement of the Industries (Development and Regulation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1971 (72 of 1971), or under section 18AA or section 18FA, that it is necessary so to do`
  line `in the interests of the general public with a view to preventing fall in the volume of production of any`
  line `scheduled industry, it may, by notified order, declare that--`
  line
  line `(a) all or any of the enactments specified in the Third Schedule shall not apply or shall apply with`
  line `such adaptations, whether by way of modification, addition or omission (which does not, however,`
  line `affect the policy of the said enactments) to such industrial undertaking, as may be specified in such`
  line `notified order, or`
  line
  line `(b) the operation of all or any of the contracts, assurances of property, agreements, settlements,`
  line `awards, standing orders or other instruments in force (to which such industrial undertaking or the`
  line `company owning such undertaking is a party or which may be applicable to such industrial`
  line `undertaking or company) immediately before the date of issue of such notified order shall remain`
  line `suspended or that all or any of the rights, privileges, obligations and liabilities accruing or arising`
  line `thereunder before the said date, shall remain suspended or shall be enforceable with such adaptations`
  line `and in such manner as may be specified in the notified order.`
  line
  line `(2) The notified order made under sub-section (1) shall remain in force, in the first instance, for a`
  line `period of one year, but the duration of such notified order may be extended from time to time by a further`
  line `notified order by a period not exceeding one year at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notified order shall, in any case, remain in force--`
  line
  line `(a) after the expiry of the period for which the management of the industrial undertaking was`
  line `taken over under section 18A, section 18AA or section 18FA, or`
  line
  line `(b) for more than ^2[eight years] in the aggregate from the date of issue of the first notified order,`
  line
  line `whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) Any notified order made under sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any other law, agreement or instrument or any decree or order of a court, tribunal,`
  line `officer or other authority or of any submission, settlement or standing order.`
  line
  line `(4) Any remedy for the enforcement of any right, privilege, obligation or liability referred to in clause`
  line `(b) of sub-section (1) and suspended or modified by a notified order made under that sub-section shall, in`
  line `accordance with the terms of the notified order, remain suspended or modified, and all proceedings`
  line `relating thereto pending before any court, tribunal, officer or other authority shall accordingly remain`
  line `stayed or be continued subject to such adaptations, so, however, that on the notified order ceasing to have`
  line effect--
  line
  line `(a) any right, privilege, obligation or liability so remaining suspended or modified shall become`
  line `revived and enforceable as if the notified order had never been made;`
  line
  line `(b) any proceeding so remaining stayed shall be proceeded with, subject to the provisions of any`
  line `law which may then be in force, from the stage which had been reached when the proceedings`
  line `became stayed.`
  line
  line `(5) In computing the period of limitation for the enforcement of any right, privilege, obligation or`
  line `liability referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1), the period during which it or the remedy for the`
  line `enforcement thereof remained suspended shall be excluded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 1979, s. 2, for "five years" (w.e.f. 30-12-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fc:
  sectionId (14200)
  sectionNo 18FC
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of Central Government to call for report on the affairs and working of managed company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fc_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14200&sectionno=18FC&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fc_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FC. Power of Central Government to call for report on the affairs and working of managed`
  line `company.--Where the management or control of an industrial undertaking has been taken over under`
  line `section 18A, whether before or after the commencement of the Industries (Development and Regulation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1971 (72 of 1971), or under section 18AA or section 18FA, the Central Government`
  line `may, at any time during the continuance of such management or control, call for a report from the`
  line `authorised person on the affairs and working of the industrial undertaking and in submitting the report the`
  line `authorised person shall take into account the inventory and the lists of members and creditors prepared`
  line `under section 18FG.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fd:
  sectionId (14201)
  sectionNo 18FD
  orderNo 33
  title `Decision of Central Government in relation to managed Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fd_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14201&sectionno=18FD&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fd_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FD. Decision of Central Government in relation to managed Company.--(1) If, on receipt of`
  line `the report submitted by the authorised person, the Central Government is satisfied,--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the company owning the industrial undertaking, which is not being wound up by`
  line `the High Court, that the financial condition and other circumstances of the company are such that it is not in a position to meet its current liabilities out of its current assets, that Government may, if it`
  line `considers necessary or expedient in the interests of the general public so to do, by order, decide that`
  line `the industrial undertaking should be sold as a running concern as provided in section 18FE and`
  line `proceedings should simultaneously be started for the winding up, by the High Court, of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the company, owning the industrial undertaking, which is being wound up by the`
  line `High Court, that its assets and liabilities are such that in the interests of its creditors and contributories`
  line `the industrial undertaking should be sold as a running concern as provided in section 18FE, it may, by`
  line `order, decide accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if, on receipt of the report submitted by`
  line `the authorised person, the Central Government is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) in the interests of the general public, or`
  line
  line `(b) in the interests of the shareholders, or`
  line
  line `(c) to secure the proper management of the company owning the industrial undertaking,`
  line
  line `it is necessary so to do, that Government may, by order, decide to prepare a scheme for the reconstruction`
  line `of the company owning the industrial undertaking:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such scheme shall be prepared in relation to a company which is being wound up by`
  line `or under the supervision of the High Court, except with the previous permission of that Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers exercisable by the Central Government under section 18F, in relation to an`
  line `undertaking taken over under section 18A, shall also be exercisable in relation to an undertaking taken`
  line `over under section 18AA or section 18FA, but such powers shall not be exercised after the making of an`
  line `order under sub-section (1) or, as the case may be, under sub-section (2) of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fe:
  sectionId (14202)
  sectionNo 18FE
  orderNo 34
  title `Provisions where Government decides to follow the course of action specified in section 18FD (1).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fe_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14202&sectionno=18FE&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fe_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FE. Provisions where Government decides to follow the course of action specified in section`
  line `18FD (1).--(1) The provisions hereinafter laid down shall apply where the Central Government decides`
  line `that the course of action specified in sub-section (1) of section 18FD should be followed, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the decision of the Central Government that the course of action specified in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) section 18FD should be followed in relation to a company owning an industrial`
  line `undertaking shall be deemed to be a ground specified in section 433 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956), on which the company may be wound up by the High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) the authorised person shall, as soon as may be, after the decision specified in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 18FD has been taken by the Central Government, present an application to`
  line `the High Court for the winding up of the company owning the industrial undertaking;`
  line
  line `(c) when an application is made by the authorised person, under clause (b), for the winding up, by`
  line `the High Court, of the company owning the industrial undertaking, the High Court shall order the`
  line `winding up of the company and shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), appoint the authorised person as the Official Liquidator in relation to such`
  line undertaking;
  line
  line `(d) whenever the Central Government decides under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18FD that the industrial undertaking should be sold as a running concern, it shall cause a copy`
  line `of its decision to be laid before the High Court;`
  line
  line `(e) until the industrial undertaking referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18FD is sold or purchased in pursuance of this section, the authorised person shall continue to`
  line `function as the Official Liquidator in relation to the said undertaking in the winding up proceedings of`
  line `the company, and thereafter the Official Liquidator appointed by the Central Government under`
  line `section 448 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall take over and function as the Official`
  line `Liquidator in the said proceedings.`
  line
  line `(2) The authorised person shall make a report to the Central Government as to what should be the`
  line `reserve price for the sale of the industrial undertaking as a running concern.`
  line
  line `(3) In making a report under sub-section (2), the authorised person shall have regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the financial condition of the company owning the industrial undertaking on the date on which`
  line `the order under section 18FD is made--`
  line
  line `(i) as disclosed in its books of account,`
  line
  line `(ii) as disclosed in its balance-sheet and profit and loss account during a period of five years`
  line `immediately preceding the said date;`
  line
  line `(b) the condition and nature of the plant, machinery, instruments and other equipment from the`
  line `point of view of their suitability for profitable use in the running of the industrial undertaking;`
  line
  line `(c) the total amount of liability on account of secured and unsecured debts including overdrafts, if`
  line `any, drawn on banks, liabilities on account of terminal benefits to the employees and other`
  line `borrowings and other liabilities of the company; and`
  line
  line `(d) other relevant factors including the factor that the industrial undertaking will be sold free from`
  line `all incumbrances.`
  line
  line `(4) Notice of the reserve price determined by the authorised person shall be given in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed to the members and creditors of the company owning such industrial undertaking to`
  line `make representations within a specified time to the Central Government through the authorised person`
  line `and the Central Government shall, after considering the representations received and the report of the`
  line `authorised person, determine the reserve price.`
  line
  line `(5) The authorised person shall thereafter, with the permission of the High Court, invite tenders from`
  line `the public in such manner as may be determined by the High Court for the sale of the industrial`
  line `undertaking as a running concern subject to the condition that it will be sold to the person offering the`
  line `highest price which shall not be less than the reserve price determined under sub-section (4):`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court shall not refuse to grant such permission if it is satisfied that the`
  line `company is not in a position to meet its current liabilities out of its current assets.`
  line
  line `(6) The industrial undertaking shall be sold to the highest bidder, as a running concern, only if the`
  line `price offered by him therefore is not less than the reserve price.`
  line
  line `(7) Where no offer of price is equal to, or more than, the reserve price, the industrial undertaking shall`
  line `be purchased by the Central Government at the reserve price.`
  line
  line `(8) (a) The amount realised from the sale of the industrial undertaking as a running concern together`
  line `with any other sum which may be realised from any contributory, purchaser or any other person from`
  line `whom any money is due to the company shall be utilised in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 to 1956), in discharging the liabilities of the company and distributing the`
  line `balance, if any, amongst the members of the company.`
  line
  line `(b) In other respects, the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), relating to the winding`
  line `up of a company by the High Court shall, as far as may be, apply.`
  line
  line `(9) When an industrial undertaking is sold to any person under sub-section (6), or purchased by the`
  line `Central Government under sub-section (7), there shall be transferred to and vested in the purchaser, free`
  line `from all incumbrances, all such assets relating to the industrial undertaking as are referred to in sub-clause`
  line `(i) of clause (a) of section 18FG and existing at the time of the sale or purchase.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_ff:
  sectionId (14203)
  sectionNo 18FF
  orderNo 35
  title `Provisions where Government decides to follow the course of action specified in section 18FD (2).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_ff_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14203&sectionno=18FF&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_ff_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FF. Provisions where Government decides to follow the course of action specified in section`
  line `18FD (2).--(1) Where in any case the Central Government decides that the course of action specified in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 18FD should be followed, it shall, subject to the provisions of that sub-section,`
  line `cause to be prepared, by the authorised person, a scheme for the reconstruction of the company, owning`
  line `the industrial undertaking, in accordance with the provisions hereinafter contained and the authorised`
  line `person shall submit the same for the approval of that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The scheme for the reconstruction of the company owning the industrial undertaking may contain`
  line `provisions for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution, name and registered office, the capital, assets, powers, rights, interests,`
  line `authorities and privileges, the liabilities, duties and obligations of the company on its reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(b) any change in the Board of directors, or the appointment of a new Board of directors of the`
  line `company on its reconstruction and the authority by whom, the manner in which and the other terms`
  line `and conditions on which, such change or appointment shall be made and in the case of appointment of`
  line `a new Board of directors or of any director, the period for which such appointment shall be made;`
  line
  line `(c) the vesting of controlling interest, in the reconstructed company, in the Central Government`
  line `either by the appointment of additional directors or by the allotment of additional shares;`
  line
  line `(d) the alteration of the memorandum and articles of association of the company, on its`
  line `reconstruction, to give effect to such reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(e) subject to the provisions of the scheme, the continuation by or against the company, on its`
  line `reconstruction, of any action or proceedings pending against the company immediately before the`
  line `date of its reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(f) the reduction of the interest or rights which the members and creditors have in or against the`
  line `company before its reconstruction to such extent as the Central Government may consider necessary`
  line `in the interests of the general public or in the interests of the members and creditors or for the`
  line `maintenance of the business of the company :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall be deemed to authorise the reduction of the`
  line `interest or rights of any creditor (including Government) in respect of any loan or advance made by`
  line `that creditor to the company after the date on which the management of the industrial undertaking of`
  line `the company has been taken over under section 18A, section 18AA, or section 18FA;`
  line
  line `(g) the payment in cash or otherwise to the creditors in full satisfaction of their claim--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of their interest or rights in or against the company before its reconstruction; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where their interest or rights in or against the company has or have been reduced under`
  line `clause (f), in respect of such interest, or rights as so reduced;`
  line
  line `(h) the allotment to the members of the company for shares held by them therein before its`
  line `reconstruction whether their interest in such shares has been reduced under clause (f) or not, of`
  line `shares in the company on its reconstruction and where it is not possible to allot shares to any`
  line `members, the payment in cash to those members in full satisfaction of their claim--`
  line
  line `(1) in respect of their interest in shares in the company before its reconstruction; or`
  line
  line `(2) where such interest has been reduced under clause (f), in respect of their interest in shares`
  line `as so reduced;`
  line
  line `(i) the offer by the Central Government to acquire by negotiations with the members of the`
  line `company their respective shares on payment in cash to those members who may volunteer to sell their`
  line `shares to the Central Government in full satisfaction of their claim--`
  line
  line `(1) in respect of their interest in shares in the company before its reconstruction; or`
  line
  line `(2) where such interest has been reduced under clause (f), in respect of their interest in shares`
  line `as so reduced;`
  line
  line `(j) the conversion of any debentures issued by the company after the taking over of the`
  line `management of the company under section 18A or section 18AA or section 18FA or of any loans`
  line `obtained by the company after that date or of any part of such debentures or loans, into shares in the`
  line `company and the allotment of those shares to such debenture-holders or creditors, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(k) the increase of the capital of the company by the issue of new shares and the allotment of such`
  line `new shares to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(l) the continuance of the services of such of the employees of the company as the Central`
  line `Government may specify in the scheme in the company itself, on its reconstruction, on such terms`
  line `and conditions as the Central Government thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(m) notwithstanding anything contained in clause (l), where any employees of the company`
  line `whose services have been continued under clause (l) have, by notice in writing given to the company`
  line `at any time before the expiry of one month next following the date on which the scheme is sanctioned`
  line `by the High Court, intimated their intention of not becoming employees of the company, on its`
  line `reconstruction, the payment to such employees and to other employees whose services have not been`
  line `continued on the reconstruction of the company, of compensation, if any, to which they are entitled`
  line `under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), and such pension, gratuity, provident fund and`
  line `other retirement benefits ordinarily admissible to them under the rules or authorisation of the`
  line `company immediately before the date of its reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(n) any other terms and conditions for the reconstruction of the company;`
  line
  line `(o) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as are necessary to secure that the`
  line `reconstruction of the company shall be fully and effectively carried out.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) A copy of the scheme, as approved by the Central Government, shall be sent in draft to the`
  line `company, to the registered trade unions, if any, of which the employees of the company are members and`
  line `to the creditors thereof for suggestions and objections, if any, within such period as the Central`
  line `Government may specify for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(b) The Central Government may make such modifications, if any, in the draft scheme as it may`
  line `consider necessary in the light of the suggestions and objections received from the company, from the`
  line `registered trade unions of which the employees of the company are members and from any members or`
  line `creditors of the company.`
  line
  line `(4) The scheme shall thereafter be placed before the High Court for its sanction and the High Court, if`
  line `satisfied that the scheme is in the interests of the general public or in the interests of the shareholders or`
  line `for securing the proper management of the company and that the scheme is designed to be fair and`
  line `reasonable to the members and creditors of the company, may, after giving a reasonable opportunity to`
  line `the company and to its members and creditors of showing cause, sanction the scheme without any`
  line `modification or with such modifications as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) The scheme, as so sanctioned by the High Court, shall come into force on such date as that Court`
  line `may specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be specified for different provisions of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(6) The sanction accorded by the High Court under sub-section (4) shall be conclusive evidence that`
  line `all the requirements of this section relating to the reconstruction of the company have been complied`
  line `with, and a copy of the sanctioned scheme certified by the High Court to be a true copy thereof, shall, in`
  line `all legal proceedings (whether original or in appeal or otherwise), be admitted as evidence to the same`
  line `extent as the original scheme.`
  line
  line `(7) On and from the date of the coming into operation of the scheme or any provision thereof, the`
  line `scheme or such provision shall be binding on the company and also on all the members and other`
  line `creditors and employees of the company and on any other person having any right or liability in relation`
  line `to the company.`
  line
  line `(8) On the coming into operation of the scheme or any provision thereof, the authorised person shall`
  line `cease to function, and the management of the reconstructed company shall be assumed by the Board of`
  line `directors as provided in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(9) Copies of the scheme shall be laid before each House of Parliament, as soon as may be, after the`
  line `scheme has been sanctioned by the Court.`
  line
  line `(10) The provisions of this section and of any scheme made thereunder shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in sections 391 to 394A (both inclusive) of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fg:
  sectionId (14204)
  sectionNo 18FG
  orderNo 36
  title `Preparation of inventory of assets and liabilities and list of members and creditors of managed company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fg_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14204&sectionno=18FG&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fg_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FG. Preparation of inventory of assets and liabilities and list of members and creditors of`
  line `managed company.--For the purposes of this Act, the authorised person shall, as soon as may be, after`
  line `taking over the management of the industrial undertaking of a company under section 18A or section`
  line `18AA or section 18FA,--`
  line
  line `(a) prepare a complete inventory of--`
  line
  line `(i) all properties, movable and immovable, including lands, buildings, works, workshops,`
  line `stores, instruments, plant, machinery, automobiles and other vehicles, stocks of materials in the`
  line `course of production, storage or transit, raw materials, cash balances, cash in hand, deposits in`
  line `bank or with any other person or body or on loan, reserve funds, investments and book debts and`
  line `all other rights and interests arising out of such property as were immediately before the date of`
  line `taking over of the industrial undertaking in the ownership, possession, power or control of the`
  line `company, whether within or without India; and all books of account, registers, maps, plans,`
  line `sections, drawings, records, documents or titles of ownership of property, and all other documents`
  line `of whatever nature relating thereto; and`
  line
  line `(ii) all borrowings, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind of the company including`
  line `liability on account of terminal benefits to its employees subsisting immediately before the said`
  line date;
  line
  line `(b) prepare separately a list of members, and a list of creditors, of such company as on the date of`
  line `taking over of the management of the industrial undertaking showing separately in the list of`
  line `creditors, the secured creditors and the unsecured creditors :`
  line
  line `Provided that where the management of the industrial undertaking of a company has been taken over`
  line `under the said section 18A before the commencement of the Industries (Development and Regulation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1971 (72 of 1971), the aforesaid functions shall be performed by the authorised person`
  line `within six months from such commencement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_fh:
  sectionId (14205)
  sectionNo 18FH
  orderNo 37
  title `Stay of suits and other proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_fh_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14205&sectionno=18FH&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_fh_content:
  string
  line `^1[18FH. Stay of suits and other proceedings.--In the case of a company in respect of which an order`
  line `under section 18FD has been made, no suit or other legal proceeding shall be instituted or continued`
  line `against the company except with the previous permission of the Central Government or any officer or`
  line `authority authorised by that Government in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_g:
  sectionId (14206)
  sectionNo 18G
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to control supply, distribution, price, etc., of certain articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14206&sectionno=18G&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_18_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[18G. Power to control supply, distribution, price, etc., of certain articles.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government, so far as it appears to it to be necessary or expedient for securing the equitable distribution`
  line `and availability at fair prices of any article or class of articles relatable to any scheduled industry, may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, by notified order, provide of`
  line `regulating the supply and distribution thereof and trade and commerce therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers conferred by sub-section (1), a notified order`
  line `made thereunder may provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for controlling the prices at which any such article or class thereof may be bought or sold;`
  line
  line `(b) for regulating by licences, permits or otherwise the distribution, transport, disposal,`
  line `acquisition, possession, use or consumption of any such article or class thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) for prohibiting the withholding from sale of any such article or class thereof ordinarily kept`
  line `for sale;`
  line
  line `(d) for requiring any person manufacturing, producing or holding in stock any such article or`
  line `class thereof to sell the whole or part of the articles so manufactured or produced during a specified`
  line `period or to sell the whole or a part of the articles so held in stock to such person or class of persons`
  line `and in such circumstances as may be specified in the order;`
  line
  line `(e) for regulating or prohibiting any class of commercial or financial transactions relating to such`
  line `article or class thereof which in the opinion of the authority making the order are, or if unregulated`
  line `are likely to be, detrimental to public interest;`
  line
  line `(f) for requiring persons engaged in the distribution and trade and commerce in any such article or`
  line `class thereof to mark the articles exposed or intended for sale with the sale price or to exhibit at some`
  line `easily accessible place on the premises the price-lists of articles held for sale and also to similarly`
  line `exhibit on the first day of every month, or at such other time as may be prescribed, a statement of the`
  line `total quantities of any such articles in stock;`
  line
  line `(g) for collecting any information or statistics with a view to regulating or prohibiting any of the`
  line `aforesaid matters; and`
  line
  line `(h) for any incidental or supplementary matters, including, in particular, the grant or issue of`
  line `licences, permits or other documents and the charging of fees therefor.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, in pursuance of any order made with reference to clause (d) of sub-section (2), any person`
  line `sells any article, there shall be paid to him the price therefor--`
  line
  line `(a) where the price can consistently with the controlled price, if any, be fixed by agreement, the`
  line `price so agreed upon;`
  line
  line `(b) where no such agreement can be reached, the price calculated with reference to the controlled`
  line `price, if any, fixed under this section;`
  line
  line `(c) where neither clause (a) nor clause (b) applies, the price calculated at the market rate`
  line `prevailing in the locality at the date of sale.`
  line
  line `(4) No order made in exercise of any power conferred by this section shall be called in question in`
  line `any court.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an order purports to have been made and signed by an authority in exercise of any power`
  line `conferred by this section, a court shall, within the meaning of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872),`
  line `presume that such order was so made by that authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expression "article or class of articles" relatable to any scheduled`
  line `industry includes any article or class of articles imported into India which is of the same nature or`
  line `description as the article or class of articles manufactured or produced in the scheduled industry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (14207)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 39
  title `Powers of inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14207&sectionno=19&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of ascertaining the position or working of any`
  line `industrial undertaking or for any other purpose mentioned in this Act or the rules made thereunder, any`
  line `person authorised by the Central Government in this behalf shall have the right--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter and inspect any premises;`
  line
  line `(b) to order the production of any document, book, register or record in the possession or power`
  line `of any person having the control of, or employed in connection with, any industrial undertaking; and`
  line
  line `(c) to examine any person having the control of, or employed in connection with, any industrial`
  line undertaking.
  line
  line `(2) Any person authorised by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a`
  line `public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (14208)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 40
  title `General prohibition of taking over management or control of industrial undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14208&sectionno=20&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `After the commencement of this Act, it shall not be competent for any State Government or a local`
  line `authority to take over the management or control of any industrial undertaking under any law for the time`
  line `being in force which authorises any such Government or local authority so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (14209)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 41
  title `Certain administrative expenses of Development Councils to be paid from moneys provided by Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14209&sectionno=21&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Such administrative expenses as relate to the emoluments of officers of a Development`
  line `Council who are appointed by or with the approval of the Central Government, shall be defrayed out of`
  line `moneys provided by Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (14210)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of the Central Government to issue directions to Development Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14210&sectionno=22&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `In the`
  line `exercise of its functions under this Act, every Development Council shall be guided by such instructions`
  line `as may be given to it by the Central Government and such instructions may include directions relating to`
  line `the manner in which, and the purpose for which, any proceeds of the cess levied under section 9 which`
  line `may have been handed over to it, shall be expanded.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (14211)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 43
  title `Decision of Central Government final respecting certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 14, for section 23 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14211&sectionno=23&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[23. Decision of Central Government final respecting certain matters.--If, for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, any question arises as to whether--`
  line
  line `(a) there has been a substantial expansion of an industrial undertaking, or`
  line
  line `(b) an industrial undertaking is producing or manufacturing any new article,`
  line
  line `the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (14212)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 44
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14212&sectionno=24&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If any person contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention`
  line of--
  line
  line `(i) the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `^2[or sub-section (4) of section 10 or of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 11 or of section 11A or of sub-section (1) of section 13 ^3[or of ^4[sub-sections (2), (2A), (2D),`
  line `(2F) and (2G) of section 29B]], or`
  line
  line `(ii) any direction issued under section 16 or sub-section (3) of section 18B, or`
  line
  line `(iii) any order made under section 18G, or`
  line
  line `(iv) any rule the contravention of which is made punishable under this section,`
  line
  line `^5[he shall be liable to penalty which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees.]]`
  line
  line `(2) If the person contravening any of the said provisions is a company, every person who at the time`
  line `the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the`
  line `business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director or manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 67 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-2-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 71 of 1956, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1984, s. 4, for "sub-section (2) of section 29B" (w.e.f. 12-1-1984).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for long line (w.e.f. 12-12-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (14213)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 45
  title Adjudication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for section 24A (w.e.f. 12-12-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14213&sectionno=24A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Adjudication.--(1) The Central Government, for the purposes of determining the penalties`
  line `under section 24, shall authorise the District Magistrate or the Additional District Magistrate, having`
  line `jurisdiction, to be the adjudicating officer, to hold an inquiry and impose penalty in the manner, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer may summon and enforce the attendance of any person acquainted with`
  line `the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any document, which in the opinion`
  line `of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for, or relevant to, the subject-matter of the inquiry and if, on`
  line `such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person concerned has failed to comply with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `he may impose such penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of section 24:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be imposed without giving the person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_b:
  sectionId (80033)
  sectionNo 24B
  orderNo 46
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=80033&sectionno=24B&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever aggrieved by the order, passed by the adjudicating officer under section`
  line `24A, may prefer an appeal to an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India,`
  line `to be an appellate authority, within thirty days from the date of receipt of order, in such form and manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period of thirty days if the appellant satisfies`
  line `the appellate authority that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) The appellate authority may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such order as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of within sixty days from the date of filing.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24_c:
  sectionId (80034)
  sectionNo 24C
  orderNo 47
  title Recovery.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=80034&sectionno=24C&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_24_c_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if penalty imposed by the`
  line `adjudicating officer under section 24A or order of the appellate authority under section 24B, as the case`
  line `may be, is not deposited, the amount shall be recovered as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (14214)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 48
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14214&sectionno=25&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Delegation of powers.--(1) The Central Government may, by notified order, direct that any`
  line `power exercisable by it under this Act (other than the power given to it by section 16^2`
  line `[,18A, 18AA and`
  line `18FA]) shall, in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the`
  line `direction, be exercisable also by such officer or authority (including in the said expressions any`
  line `Development Council, State Government or officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government)`
  line `as may be specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(2) Any power exercisable by a State Government by virtue of a direction under sub-section (1) may,`
  line `unless otherwise provided in such direction, be exercised also by such officer or authority subordinate to`
  line `that State Government as it may, by notified order, specify in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sections 25 to 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 7, for "and 18A" (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (14215)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sections 25 to 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14215&sectionno=26&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Power to issue directions.--The Central Government may give directions to any State`
  line `Government as to the carrying into execution in the State of any of the provisions of this Act or of any`
  line `order or direction made thereunder.]`
