obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (14220)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to exempt in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14220&sectionno=29B&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[29B. Power to exempt in special cases.--^2[(1)] If the Central Government is of opinion, having`
  line `regard to the smallness of the number of workers employed or to the amount invested in any industrial`
  line `undertaking or to the desirability of encouraging small undertakings generally or to the stage of`
  line `development of any scheduled industry, that it would not be in public interest to apply all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act thereto, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt, subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose, any industrial undertaking or class of industrial undertakings or`
  line `any scheduled industry or class of scheduled industries as it may specify in the notification from the`
  line `operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Where any notification under sub-section (1) granting any exemption is cancelled, no owner of`
  line `any industrial undertaking to which the provisions of section 10, section 11, section 11A or clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13 would have applied, if the notification under sub-section (1) had not been`
  line `issued, shall carry on the business of the undertaking after the expiry of such period as may be specified`
  line `in the notification cancelling the exemption except under and in accordance with a licence issued in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government and, in the case of a State Government, except under and in accordance`
  line `with the previous permission of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^4[(2A) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `Central Government may, if it is satisfied, after considering the recommendations made to it by the`
  line `Advisory Committee constituted under sub-section (2B), that it is necessary so to do for the development`
  line `and expansion of ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings, by notified order, direct that any article`
  line `or class of articles specified in the First Schedule shall, on and from such date as may be specified in the`
  line `notified order (hereafter in this section referred to as the "date of reservation"), be reserved for exclusive`
  line `production by the ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings (hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `"reserved article").`
  line
  line `(2B) The Central Government shall, with a view to determining the nature of any article or class of`
  line `articles that may be reserved for production by the ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings,`
  line `constitute an Advisory Committee consisting of such persons as have, in the opinion of that Government,`
  line `the necessary expertise to give advice on the matter.`
  line
  line `(2C) The Advisory Committee shall, after considering the following matters, communicate its`
  line `recommendations to the Central Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of any article or class of articles which may be produced economically by the`
  line `ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings;`
  line
  line `(b) the level of employment likely to be generated by the production of such article or class of`
  line `articles by the ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings;`
  line
  line `(c) the possibility of encouraging and diffusing entrepreneurship in industry;`
  line
  line `(d) the prevention of concentration of economic power to the common detriment; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as the Advisory Committee may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2D) The production of any reserved article or class of reserved articles by any industrial undertaking`
  line `(not being an ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertaking) which, on the date of reservation, is`
  line `engaged in, or has taken effective steps for, the production of any reserved article or class of reserved`
  line `articles, shall, after the commencement of the Industries (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act,`
  line `1984 (4 of 1984), or, as the case may be, the date of reservation, whichever is later, be subject to such`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may, by notified order, specify.`
  line
  line `(2E) While specifying any condition under sub-section (2D), the Central Government may take into`
  line `consideration the level of production of any reserved article or class of reserved articles achieved,`
  line `immediately before the date of reservation, by the industrial undertaking referred to in sub-section (2D),`
  line `and such other factors as may be relevant.`
  line
  line `(2F) Every person or authority, not being the Central Government, who, or which, is registered under`
  line `section 10 or to whom, or to which, a licence has been issued or permission has been granted under`
  line `section 11 for the production of any article or class of articles which has, or have, been subsequently`
  line `reserved for the ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings, shall produce, such registration`
  line `certificate, licence or permission, as the case may be, within such period as the Central Government may,by notified order, specify in this behalf, and the Central Government may enter therein all or any of`
  line `the conditions specified by it under sub-section (2D), including the productive capacity of the industrial`
  line `undertakings and other prescribed particulars.`
  line
  line `(2G) The owner of every industrial undertaking (not being an ancillary or small scale, industrial`
  line `undertaking) which, immediately before the commencement of the Industries (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Amendment Act, 1984 (4 of 1984), or the date of reservation, whichever is later,--`
  line
  line `(a) was engaged in the production of any article or class of articles, which has, or have, been`
  line `reserved for the ancillary, or small scale, industrial undertakings, or`
  line
  line `(b) had before such commencement or before the date of such reservation, as the case may be,`
  line `taken effective steps for commencing the production of such reserved article or class of reserved`
  line articles,
  line
  line `without being registered under section 10 or in respect of which a licence or permission has not been`
  line `issued under section 11, shall refrain from the production of such reserved article or class of reserved`
  line `articles, on and from the date of expiry of three months from such commencement or from the date of`
  line `such reservation, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(2H) Every notified order made under sub-section (2A) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notified order or both Houses agree that the notified order should not be made, the`
  line `notified order shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notified order.]`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act shall apply, so far as may be, in relation to the issue of a licence or`
  line `permission to any industrial undertaking referred to in sub-section (2) as they apply in relation to the issue`
  line `of a licence or permission to a new industrial undertaking.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sections 25 to 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Section 29B re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 71 of 1956, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 71 of 1956, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-1-1984)`
obj_root_law_sections_29_c:
  sectionId (14221)
  sectionNo 29C
  orderNo 55
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sections 25 to 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953)./`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14221&sectionno=29C&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[29C. Protection of action taken under the Act.--(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act`
  line `or any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government for any damage caused or likely`
  line `to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or`
  line `any rule or order made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_d:
  sectionId (14222)
  sectionNo 29D
  orderNo 56
  title `Debts incurred by the authorised person to have priority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14222&sectionno=29D&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_29_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[29D. Debts incurred by the authorised person to have priority.--Every debt arising out of any`
  line `loan obtained by the authorised person for carrying on the management of, or exercising function of`
  line `control in relation to, an industrial undertaking or part thereof, the management of which has been taken`
  line `over under section 18A or section 18AA or section 18FA,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall have priority over all other debts, whether secured or unsecured, incurred before the`
  line `management of such industrial undertaking was taken over;`
  line
  line `(b) shall be a preferential debt within the meaning of section 530 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1`
  line `of 1956),`
  line
  line `and such debts shall rank equally among themselves and be paid in full out of the assets of the industrial`
  line `undertakings unless such assets are insufficient to meet them, in which case they shall abate in equal`
  line proportions.]
obj_root_law_sections_29_e:
  sectionId (14223)
  sectionNo 29E
  orderNo 57
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2016, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14223&sectionno=29E&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_29_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[29E. Validation.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, decree or order of any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority, any power exercised, or action taken or done or purported to have been`
  line `taken or done, by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government, shall be deemed`
  line `to be, and shall always deemed to have been, for all purposes, as validly taken or done or omitted to be`
  line `done, as if the amendment made to the First Schedule by the Industries (Development and Regulation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 2016 had been in force at all material times and no suit or claim or other proceedings`
  line `shall be instituted, maintained or continued in any court, tribunal or other authority as such.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (14224)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166&sectionId=14224&sectionno=30&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00006_195165_1517807327166
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to the condition of previous`
  line `publication, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution of the Advisory Council and Development Councils, the term of office and`
  line `other conditions of service of, the procedure to be followed by, and the manner of filling casual`
  line `vacancies among members of the Advisory Council or a Development Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of the statement of account to be furnished by a Development Council;`
  line
  line `(c) the intervals at which, the time within which, and the manner in which the cess leviable under`
  line `section 9 shall be payable and the rebate for the prompt payment of such cess;`
  line
  line `(d) the expenses which a Development Council may meet from the proceeds of the cess levied`
  line `under section 9 which may have been handed over to it;`
  line
  line `(e) the appointment by or with the approval of the Central Government of any officers of a`
  line `Development Council;`
  line
  line `(f) the facilities to be provided by any industrial undertaking for the training of technicians and`
  line labour;
  line
  line `(g) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of any scheduled industry;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which industrial undertakings may be registered under section 10 and the levy`
  line `of a fee therefor;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for the grant or issue of licences and permissions under^1[section 11,`
  line `section 11A^2[section 13 or section 29B]], the time within which such licences or permissions shall be`
  line `granted or issued including, in particular, the publication of notices calling for applications and the`
  line `holding of such public inquiry in relation thereto as may be necessary in the circumstances;`
  line
  line `(j) the fees to be levied in respect of licences and permissions issued under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) the matters which may be taken into account in the granting or issuing of licences and`
  line `permissions, including in particular, the previous consultation by the Central Government with the`
  line `Advisory Council or any Development Council or both in regard to the grant or issue of any such`
  line `licences or permission;`
  line
  line `(l) the procedure to be followed in making any investigation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) the conditions which may be included in any licences and permissions;`
  line
  line `(n) the conditions on which licences and permissions may be varied or amended under section 12;`
  line
  line `(o) the maintenance of books, accounts and records relating to an industrial undertaking;`
  line
  line `(p) the submission of special or periodical returns relating to an industrial undertaking by persons`
  line `having the control of, or employed in connection with, such undertaking, and the forms in which, and`
  line `the authorities to which, such returns and reports shall be submitted;`
  line
  line `^3[(pp) any matter which is to be or may be prescribed for giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `Chapter IIIAA or Chapter IIIAC;]`
  line
  line `^4[(ppa) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under sub-section (1) of section 24A;`
  line
  line `(ppb) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (1) of section 24B;]`
  line `(q) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under this section may provide that a contravention thereof shall be ^5[liable to`
  line `penalty] under section 24.`
  line
  line `^6[(4) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1953, s. 18, for "section 11 or section 13" (w.e.f. 1-10-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 71 of 1956, s. 6, for "or section 13" (w.e.f. 1-3-1957).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 72 of 1971, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-11-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 12-12-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for "punishable" (w.e.f. 12-12-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
